    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Remember, if you make a mistake (perhaps by providing an incorrect type of parameter), you&apos;ll most likely bring up a walkback. This protects you from doing any real damage. If this happens, simply click </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Terminate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to continue and then try to fix the problem. If you really get into trouble you should be able to clean things up by closing the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Playground</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> window and the associated workspace and starting again.</text></para>
